tags.description: This is a small rock fissure where part of the cliff has moved away from the main mass forming a narrow passage with two exits/entrances. The interior features crude carved intials of "D. O."
tags.name: Craigneith Cranny

tags.description: Crutherland Cave was named in the late 2000s by Chris Ladds, an East Kilbride based historian. Prior to that time it is unclear what if any formal name it had. It was referred to at least two times in the latter half of the 1800s as Wallaces Cave.
tags.name: Crutherland Cave
